Sentencas: In this work, anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) were tested with a yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) (8 mol% Y2O3-ZrO2)/gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) (Ce0.9Gd O-0.1(1.95)) bilayer electrolyte and two lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) composition as functional cathode layer: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF 1) and La0.60Sr0.40Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF 2).
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The functional cathode layers were made of 50 % (w/w) LSCF and 50 % (w/w) GDC.
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Microstructural characterization was performed by scanning electron microscopy and X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) and power measurements were performed under oxygen and hydrogen atmospheres.
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microscopy studies showed that the LSCF 2 functional layer is more uniform and adherent to the electrolyte and the cathode collector than the LSCF 1 functional layer, which has cracks, chips, and lower adhesion.
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The use of the LSCF 2 layer allowed an approximately 25-fold reduction in ohmic resistance (0.06 abroken vertical bar cm(-2)) compared with the LSCF 1 layer (1.5 abroken vertical bar cm(-2)).
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power measurements showed a considerable increase in the power cell using LSCF 2 (approximately 420 mW cm(-2)) compared with the power cell using LSCF 1 (approximately 180 mW cm(-2)).
Titulo: Influence of cathode functional layer composition on electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells
